[Black "Chapter 3 Scheveningen Formation II"]

{In this second Scheveningen chapter, Black steps off the d-file with ...Qc7, with or without ...a6 inserted. White responds with Bf4, posting the bishop opposite Black's queen and putting pressure on d6.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 d6 6. Bc4 e6 7. O-O Be7 8. Qe2 {[%entry]} a6 (8... Nf6 9. Rd1 Qc7 10. Nb5 Qb8 11. Bf4 Ne5?! (11... e5 12. Bg5 a6 (12... O-O 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 (13... gxf6? 14. Nh4) 14. Nxd6) 13. Bxf6 axb5 (13... gxf6 14. Nc3) 14. Bxe7 Kxe7) 12. Nxd6+ Bxd6 13. Rxd6 Qxd6 14. Bxe5) 9. Rd1 Qc7 10. Bf4 Nf6 (10... Ne5? 11. Bxe5 dxe5 12. Bb5+! axb5 13. Nxb5 Qb6 14. Nxe5 Nf6 15. Nc4) 11. Rac1 O-O 12. Bb3 Qb8 (12... Rd8 13. Nd5 exd5 14. exd5) (12... Nh5 13. Be3) 13. e5 Nh5 14. Bg5 dxe5 15. Bxe7 Nxe7 16. Nxe5 *
